news.title: LED street lights project in Hubballi-Dharwad in limbo despite government's approval
news.para: Despite government approvals on August 18, Hubballi-Dharwad's ambitious LED street light project remains stalled, highlighting a significant implementation gap. The Rs 93.5 crore PPP initiative aims to replace 64,000 lamps, promising energy savings and improved city management, but bureaucratic delays are hindering progress.

news.title: FIR against 90 for construction on land notified for Noida airport
news.para: Ninety residents in Jewar face FIRs for unauthorized construction on land designated for the Noida International Airport expansion. Despite repeated warnings and monitoring, villagers proceeded with building new structures and additions after land notification, aiming to inflate compensation claims. The FIR aims to deter further violations and enable demolition of illegal constructions.

news.title: NA tax scrapping awaits GR a year after cabinet nod; Pune societies continue to receive notices
news.para: Housing societies in Pune and Mumbai are still waiting for an official government order to abolish the non-agricultural tax. The state cabinet approved the move last October. However, the delay in issuing the government resolution means many societies are still receiving tax notices and some are paying to avoid action.

news.title: ED attaches ₹12 crore assets of Sahiti Infratec in ₹842 crore fraud case
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has attached properties valued at ₹12.6 crore linked to Sahiti Infratec Ventures India Private Limited and its former director Sandu Purnachandra Rao. This action follows investigations into allegations of defrauding investors of ₹842 crore. Funds collected from homebuyers were reportedly diverted for personal use. Earlier, assets worth ₹161 crore were attached.

news.title: Delhi fire department seeks revised plan for GPRA colony
news.para: Delhi Fire Services has rejected building plans for the Sarojini Nagar GPRA colony due to serious non-compliance with the National Building Code. Deficiencies include inadequate building access, fire exits, hydrant placement, and escape route width. The developer must rectify these issues and resubmit revised plans.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Phase I of Rajaji Nagar rehabilitation to begin in November 2025
news.para: Rehabilitation of 32 families into a new residential complex at Rajaji Nagar is set to begin in November, marking a significant milestone in the area's revitalization. The four-storey, 2BHK apartment block, costing Rs 9 crore, is nearing completion with finishing works underway. This initial phase will see displaced families moving into upgraded infrastructure, with potential for future expansion.

news.title: Brigade Hotel Ventures' net profit up 58% in Q2 FY26
news.para: Brigade Hotel Ventures (BHVL) reported a significant 57.97% jump in net consolidated profit for Q2 FY26, reaching ₹10.60 crore. The company's total income also grew by 19.70% to ₹129.80 crore. BHVL plans to double its hotel portfolio by FY30 with a ₹3,600 crore investment, adding 9 new properties.

news.title: DDA's retroactive GST on property conversion challenged in Delhi HC
news.para: A resident of Delhi has stepped into the courtroom, taking a stand against the Delhi Development Authority over its decision to apply Goods and Services Tax retroactively on property conversions. This retrospective tax impacts property owners who switched to freehold status after 2017. The petitioner maintains that the DDA's approach is unconstitutional and violates basic rights.

news.title: Google leases 6.17 lakh sq ft office space in Gurugram
news.para: US tech giant Google has secured a significant office space of 617,000 sq ft in Gurugram. This major deal at Atrium Place highlights Google's expanding presence in India. The company is committed to growing its operations and office footprint. This move follows previous leasing activities by Google in the region.

news.title: Nagpur to get BKC-style commercial hub at Kachipura with housing for 800 families
news.para: Union Minister Nitin Gadkari announced plans for a Mumbai-style commercial hub on 19 hectares of encroached land in Nagpur. The project will include inclusive rehabilitation for 800 families and offer commercial space at reasonable rates. This development aims to boost Nagpur's economic infrastructure and serve as a model for inclusive urban growth.

news.title: Lucknow development body extends discount offer on ready-to-move flats
news.para: Lucknow Development Authority has extended its special Diwali discount offer on ready-to-move flats until November 6. Buyers can now avail direct discounts ranging from Rs 1 lakh to Rs 2 lakh. This festive season has already seen 589 flats booked. Over 1,100 ready-to-move flats are still available for interested buyers across various LDA schemes.

news.title: About 441 hectares from 18 villages now officially with YEIDA
news.para: YEIDA has officially registered 441 hectares of land across 18 Jewar villages in its name, resolving a years-long issue of unrecorded ownership. This move aims to prevent illegal sales and cultivation on acquired land, ensuring public assets are protected from misuse and fraud.

news.title: Delhi: 1,537 flats to be offered under DDA’s scheme
news.para: Delhi Development Authority is launching Phase II of the Jan Sadharan Awas Yojana on November 11.  This offers 1,537 affordable flats for low-income and economically weaker sections.  The flats are located in areas like Shivaji Marg, Ramgarh Colony, Rohini, and Narela.  Registration opens at noon on November 11.  Bookings will be on a first-come, first-served basis.

news.title: Frustrated owners push for Karnataka Apartment Ownership Act overhaul
news.para: Appealing to the government directly, Vani Kishore, a home buyer, said she wanted the long-awaited act to enable apartment associations to register under a competent authority.

news.title: Builders must reserve 15% flats for EWS buyers in Haryana
news.para: Haryana has introduced a new policy for EWS housing, mandating developers reserve 20% of plots and 15% of flats for economically weaker sections. The Housing for All department will now handle allotments transparently, with a five-year lock-in period to prevent speculation and ensure benefits reach genuine low-income families.

news.title: Australia's Westpac unit fined $13 million for home loans misconduct
news.para: In a significant ruling, Australia's Federal Court has imposed a hefty A$20 million fine on the RAMS Financial Group, a subsidiary of Westpac. This penalty arises from alarming practices in home loan arrangements, where the company resorted to the use of fake payslips and engaged with unlicensed referral agents.

news.title: Holcim recurring operating profit rise by 8.1% in Q3 2025
news.para: Holcim has revealed a slight uptick in profits, driven by its dedication to premium offerings like low-carbon cement and eco-friendly concrete. This strategic pivot has effectively countered the challenges posed by a robust Swiss franc. The company's recurring operating profits have grown in local currencies, and it confidently stands by its financial forecast for the year.

news.title: Ikea leases 37,000 sq ft store in a Pune mall
news.para: Swedish furniture giant Ikea is set to enter Pune. The company has leased a significant space in Phoenix Marketcity mall. The lease agreement is for 59 months. It already has a presence in several Indian cities.

news.title: Mumbai builders meet civic chief to discuss real estate bottlenecks & propose premium payment reforms
news.para: Mumbai's real estate sector is set for a boost. Top developers met with Municipal Commissioner Bhushan Gagrani. They discussed issues affecting the industry. A new steering committee will now meet fortnightly. This aims to resolve problems and improve processes. A new premium payment structure is proposed. This will ease financial burdens on developers.
